steps.section: REM sleep behavior disorder scoring and periodogram analyses
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"e0rdu","text":"Following the scoring of sleep stages, convert the EMG into the root mean square (RMS) using the signal grid function. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: REM sleep behavior disorder scoring and periodogram analyses
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4cv0a","text":"For all recordings, generate a signal grid, including the timestamps (20s windows) of the GMT time, the RMS of the EMG, the sleep scoring, and the EEG. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: REM sleep behavior disorder scoring and periodogram analyses
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"3efn","text":"Obtain a periodogram Power Band (PB) for each 20s window within the 0.3 to 80 Hz band range. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: REM sleep behavior disorder scoring and periodogram analyses
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"65b3j","text":"Employ a 10/1024 FFT order, an overlap of 50%, and a Hamming spectral function applied to the window. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: REM sleep behavior disorder scoring and periodogram analyses
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4ts0e","text":"Express PB values as a relative percentage of the power band value. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"avqj7","text":"Determine the:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1eqpb","text":"Delta oscillation within the 0.5 to 4Hz window","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a6tn8","text":"Theta within the 4 to 8Hz window","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6129s","text":"Alpha within the 8 to 12Hz window","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"99aib","text":"Sigma within the 12 to 16Hz window","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8ksj","text":"Beta within the 16 to 24Hz window","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fb0ib","text":"Low Gamma within the 24 to 49 Hz window","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a3n0h","text":"High Gamma within the 51 to 80Hz window","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: REM sleep behavior disorder scoring and periodogram analyses
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"9jkf","text":"For each sleep, awake, and REM event, extract and analyze the average PB value for\neach band-pass frequency. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"185i","text":"In Excel, convert the RMS-EMG to the z-score over the entire recording.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: REM sleep behavior disorder scoring and periodogram analyses
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"bdp5","text":"Use a COUNTIF function to count the number of REM events (scored as P), awake events (scored as W), or NREM events (scored as S) for the entire recording, as well as during the dark/light phases.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
